# toc_auto.lt -- locks in the Lout source mdlout emits for a [TOC]
# placeholder. Because Lout's `doc` setup has no per-position TOC
# macro, mdlout currently leaves a comment in the Lout stream and
# delegates the visible TOC to the HTML wrapper (HTML mode) or to the
# `contents: Yes` frontmatter switch on report/book setups (PDF mode).
# This snippet just exercises the Lout side -- the marker has to
# survive the round trip without breaking subsequent paragraph layout.
@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
First paragraph above the TOC marker.
# [Table of Contents placeholder]
@PP
Paragraph after the marker; layout should be unaffected.
@End @Text
